cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in computational pathology, specifically in addressing the issue of stain variation in histopathology images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses techniques for reducing generalization error in CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of unsupervised methods for stain color normalization involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of stain color normalization for improving image retrieval, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with histopathology images, which are a type of medical imaging, and therefore could also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
